  h2(id="protocol-pcr-cleanup") PCR clean-up<ref authors="Promega" title="Wizard&reg; SV Gel and PCR Clean-Up System" url="https://ch.promega.com/products/nucleic-acid-extraction/clean-up-and-concentration/wizard-sv-gel-and-pcr-clean-up-system" />

  h3 Gel slice and PCR product preparation
  ol
    li
      | Dissolving the gel slice
      ol
        li: p Following electrophoresis, excise DNA band from gel and place gel slice in a 1.5 ml microcentrifuge tube.
        li: p Add 10 µl Membrane Binding Solution per 10 mg of gel slice. Vortex and incubate at 50 &ndash; 65°C until gel slice is completely dissolved.
    li
      | Processing PCR amplifications
      ol
        li: p Add an equal volume of Membrane Binding Solution to the PCR amplification.

  h3 Binding of DNA
  ol
    li: p Insert SV Minicolumn into Collection Tube.
    li: p Transfer dissolved gel mixture or prepared PCR product to the Minicolumn assembly. Incubate at room temperature for 1 minute.
    li: p Centrifuge at 16,000 g for 1 minute. Discard flowthrough and reinsert Minicolumn into Collection Tube.

  h3 Washing
  ol
    li: p Add 700 µl Membrane Wash Solution (ethanol added). Centrifuge at 16,000 g for 1 minute. Discard flowthrough and reinsert Minicolumn into Collection Tube.
    li: p Repeat Step 4 with 500 µl Membrane Wash Solution. Centrifuge at 16,000 g for 5 minutes.
    li: p Empty the Collection Tube and recentrifuge the column assembly for 1 minute with the microcentrifuge lid open (or off) to allow evaporation of any residual ethanol.

  h3 Elution
  ol
    li: p Carefully transfer Minicolumn to a clean 1.5 ml microcentrifuge tube.
    li: p Add 50 µl of Nuclease-Free Water to the Minicolumn. Incubate at room temperature for 1 minute. Centrifuge at 16,000 g for 1 minute.
    li: p Discard Minicolumn and store DNA at 4°C or -20°C.



  h2(id="protocol-western-blot") Western blot

  h3 Materials
  ul
    li Lysis Buffer: 0.1 M NaOH, 0.05M EDTA, 2% SDS, 2% Beta-mercapto-EtOH (ex: for V = 10 ml, 100 µl of NaOH 10M, 146 mg of EDTA, 1 ml of 20% SDS and 200 µl beta-mercapto, complete with dH2O)
    li Loading buffer: 0.25 M Tris-HCl, 50% glycerol, 0.05% Bromophenol Blue (ex: for V = 10 ml, 2.5 ml of 1 M Tri-HCl, 5 ml glycerol and 5 mg bromophenol blue, complete with dH2O)

  h3 Tissue lysis and buffer extraction
  ol
    li: p Collect 10<sup>8</sup> yeast cells for each sample (e.g. prepare a solution 1.5 ml of OD600 = 1.6 and pellet using centrifuge).
    li: p Resuspend in 200 µl lysis buffer.
    li: p Boil 10 minutes at 90°C.
    li: p Add 5 µl of 4 M acetic acid and vortex.
    li: p Boil 10 minutes at 90°C.
    li: p Add 50 µl of loading buffer.

  h3 Gel run
  ol
    li: p Preparing the gels: remove plastic, rinse away salts in dH<sub>2</sub>O, fill chambers with 2X running buffer.
    li: p Load in wells (30 &ndash; 40 µl/well for 10 wells/gel). Load four times less 4X loading buffer in empty wells (e.g. 10 µl), same for the ladder.
    li: p Run gel 120 V until protein size is low on the gel.
    li: p Bend gel using a metal tool to remove the gel from plastic, cut away unnecessary gel.

  h3 Blotting
  ol
    li: p Put the gel in water on the shaker for one minute, then use iBlot for the transfer.

  h3 Staining
  ol
    li: p Wash the membrane with PBS-TX and stain with Ponceau S solution for 10 &ndash; 15 minutes.
    li: p Cut around where the protein is stained.
    li: p Wash with PBS-TX (3x 5 min) and block with fresh PBS-TX 0.1% Milk 5% (e.g. 2.5 g in 50 ml PBS-TX) for 30 min &ndash; 1 hour.
    li: p Incubate the primary antibody(ies) O/N at 4°C or 1h30-2h at RT.
    li: p Wash 3x 5 min with PBS-TX.
    li: p Incubate the secondary antibody(ies) for 1 hour at RT.
    li: p Wash 3x 5 min with PBS-TX.

  h3 Imaging
  ol
    li: p Prepare the chemiluminescent substrate by mixing each WesternBright Sirius<ref authors="Advansta" title="WesternBright Sirius HRP substrate" url="https://products.advansta.com/western-blot-substrate-WesternBright_Sirius/" /> solution (2X) together (1 ml each).
    li: p Put membrane on the table after drying a little bit on Kleenex.
    li: p Dispense the solution homogeneously on the membrane for 5 min.
    li: p Dry a little on Kleenex and put in plastic. Turn on Imager and expose.

  h3 Stripping (removal of primary and secondary antibodies from the membrane)
  p If you are planning to keep the membrane for further analyses:
  ol
    li: p Place the blot in Restore Western Blot Stripping Buffer and incubate for 5 to 15 minutes at 37°C.
    li: p Remove the blot from the Restore Western Blot Stripping Buffer and wash with PBS-TX.



